AGI - The mayor of Istanbul Ekrem Imamoglu has defined "made to art and without foundation" the accusations of corruption and ties with the terrorist organization Pkk that determined its arrest. Waiting for the deposition before the judges scheduled this evening, the mayor of the metropolis on the Bosphorus entrusted a message to the town he led from 2019.
&nbsp;
"The immoral and foundational accusations that have been addressed to me are based on art-made evidence to embarrass the investigation and aim to strike my reputation and credibility. What is happening is harming Turkey's image on the international level, it removes people's confidence in justice and affects the economy. Those who hide behind all this will have to answer them before a court. With the strength of the millions of people who support me I will continue to fight for justice and truth until the end of my life," said Imamoglu in this message spread by the municipality. &nbsp;
<h2>Imamoglu in court, new clashes in Istanbul</h2>
Imamoglu began his deposition before the judges of a Istanbul court and the tension between the supporters of the first citizen of the metropolis on the Bosphorus and the police went to the stars. A group of lawyers tried to enter the courthouse, except to find the road disembarked by a police cordon that rejected them with force.
The Turkish police intervened with hydrants and tear gases also to disperse parades of protesters intent on heading towards the armored area of the Palace of Justice. Scontri are also taking place in the Sarachane area, where the municipality of Istanbul is located. Neighborhood from three days to the center of protests undecided by the opposition to protest against the arrest of the mayor.&nbsp;
